76561197980125232,Not Recommended,219780,28153066,"Posted: 2 December, 2016",all,Morte,"* ignore my time played, I am at least 20 hours not logged in steam, will explain later.There are 2 reasons I can't recommend this game.The first is the horrrible game balance issues.  Enemies do not respawn in this game which means there is limited gold/xp in the world.  This means if you do not build your character correctly it is possible to get stuck in the game as you have no ways to improve your character to take on certain fights.  Also health and mana regen extremely slowly so if you are using melee or magic you end up just standing around waiting until you are ready to take on the next fight.  An increased regen out of combat could have fixed this.  Other than these issues from a gameplay perspective the game is reasonable.  The interesting part of the game that the game sells itself on is the ability to turn into a dragon yet you only gain this abillity half way through the game.Secondly there are technical issues running this on newer versions of windown (definintely windows 10, possibly 7 and 8).  If using win10 the game will lock up after 2 world transitions.  This makes it very painful to play as you need to contantly save before every door.  I was able to fix this by using a 3rd party program to hack the executable to use 4gm ram however this also resulted in the game not running from the launcher and had to be run directly which resulted in the game not working with steam ui or logging time.  I also discovered that during the install process the game installs an old version of PhysX regardless of whether you have a current version.  This then causes games such as Mass Effect 2 and 3 to crash on start until you uninstall the old version that Divinity 2 installs."
