,Recommended,219780,28601848,"Posted: 24 December, 2016",all,Cambionn,"I love this game. It's the first that stopped me from playing/modding elder scrolls completly until finished since BioShock Infinte. It's a typical old-school RPG, but a damn good one. I don't think it's really hard, nor easy. Seems just about the right difficualty too me. It has a nice storyline, the kind of humour I love from RPGs (like the guy who's SoulForced with a chicken, or the ability to spread pretty bad rumours) and gives some unique features like mind reading and becoming a dragon. It's somewhat old but it does still work well gameplay wise.I havn't had any problem with balancing. Regen starts slow, but the game is pretty easy at that point, and with the right armours and skills it can become quite fast (I never used potions during this game, I just jump arround until my health is refilled). Just like in elder scrolls, it's possible to mix and match all RPG classes, so you're not limited to warrior, rogue or mage. After you have become a dragon, you will be able to reset your skills (at that point it costed me at most 10% of my in-game money, pretty cheap, but price will go up every time you do it), so little misstakes and skills you tried but didn't like can easily be fixed. There is indeed no respawn in this game, so limited gold an XP, but I managed to stay overleveld during the game. I defiantly got more gold and XP then needed and also have been able to beat places that where 5 levels above mine, so it's not really a problem. I actually think you'll become overleveld easily if respawning would be included.The only downsides I have is that the in-game AA doesn't work (like there is an option but it doesn't do anything), and that shadows on characters are horribly blocky (but environment is great). Turned shadows off and made some Re-Shade preset (which I also gave some Ambient Occlusion to fake shadows) and it looks quite decent, considering it's release date.Next to that the game has an issues with newer(mainly faster) hardware. It will tear on 60FPS (because my hardware is rendering faster then the engine can handle). Capping the game at 30 easily fixed the problem and makes the game look smooth again. Otherwise I haven't found any issues on performance (running Windows10, gtx1080 (2000+MHz), i5-6600K (4.2GHz), 16GB DDR4).Also the autosave is horrible. It only saves before some plot parts for main storyline. If you die you will have to reload a save, so it would be good to get used to saving manually often.Still, my biggest archievement in this game is when I find some pants that have good stats for my level, because Larian loves miniskirts it seems. Just makes me think someone forgot to put on her pants/leg protection in the morning."
