76561198026942737,Recommended,219780,17098390,"Posted: 17 July, 2015",all,madgamer2,"Tqake everything you think you know about RPG games,  YOU KNOW THE WAY THEY ARE DESIGNED AND PLAYED,  All the dungeon crawling, leveling up and game play and put them in a bag and toss them into the trash.   Because the way you see and play and invole yoursel with the game will be changed forever.It starts out with you being a new dragon slayer and going to a place called Farglow to learn the basics of dragon slaying.   You will choose what class you want to be.  There are 3 here to choose from: MAGE,  FIGHTER,and RANGER.SOME HAVE SAID THAT CHARACTER CHOICE AND CREATION RUN ALONG THE SIMPLE.   I think you will develop your character through the choice of over 30 skills which are devided into the three mentioned clases plus a priest class.   The basic development fall into two basic ways to develop your character.You can develop a  character using skills from his class or you cat develop one using skill choices from several classes.This will let you develop a character that suits your style.  A single class character will be stronger and a character developed using skill from more than one class  will be more visital,    I started as a fighter but soon saw the advantageto being good with a bow.  Keep in mind that your class choice  will give you some skills to start the game depending on the class.The skills are devided into 2 types active and passive.  You can have as many passive skills as yo wish,  The active skills and other items are placed in a 8 hotkey display at the bottom of the screen.  You can have more active skill and special abilities but only 8 will be in the hotkeys. The special ability's things you can do,Each time you gain a level you get 6 stat points  that you can increase one of your 5 ststs.  You also get 1 skill points to purchase a new skill or improve an exsisting skill,   Each skill has 5 levels till later in the game.  Take note with just onepoint/turn you will have to learn the hard way that once you make a choice it can not be changed till later in the game.Because of the way this game levelup and does not use the game levels are based on your level some interesting things happen.  If you get into a situation where your character is higher that the NPC monsters then you may have abattle where the NPC gets his lickls and you get a small number of xp points or eve 0,  Which  leads to the practice of witholding stat points and even skill points till you come acxross NPC's who give you more xp points.  This may sound strange but in playing the gqame it does work.  I like it because it limits the practice of ""Power Leveling"" The way the game levels is something you should take at face value like many of the game  mechcanics work in the game if you just usr them and in time it will let you see what a marvolus game this is...It is hard but ther is always a way.Now the combat will really be frustrating at first.  You do not have nice turn based combat because it is real time.When you get into the second part of the game in the begining section you will encounter large groups of hostile NPC'sand will have to develop ways to deal with them.   Once an area or a group of units is dead they stay that way.There is the run in ....kill a couple..aned try to get out into a safe place. save and repeat.Different movement skills are used in the game to solve problems and quests.  Once again this is not the normal thing in many RPG's.   For example  there are many kinds of containers to open and a bright yellow light will occur if  something can be opened including  some empty containers.  Now depending on the angle of you mouse and how your character is this  yellow light may not always show up. Moving you character slowly in each direction will help.  Also a messahe will apear next to the hotkey area and tell you there is something to open or use or take.  One of the more difficult things you will have to learn is jumping.  Many quests have platforms to jump from one to the next and some platfors arte moving,  There is a learning curve if you are using a mouse and keyboard (controlers  are not enabled for the most partThere are many wepons, armor inchantments, charms, and pluses for stats that you will be able to use depending on you level.  There are some who do not like the armor methods used in the game because they can't  get matching sets.  I find no ewason to comment on this because the absurdity is plain to see. It is possible to taloy your character in many different way to reach a certain result.  If you find a situation that call for an archer, maage or whatever then you cause rifferent selections of eqyuipment, to get the job done.I think this is a great game with many vqarid and challanging  problems.   It never fails to have me shaking  my head.  The graphics are just right for the game theyare neither to strong or two week.   One thing that I have never seen in an RPG is the notebook tab.  Her yoyu wil;l find several very useful  features,   Thgere is one that has all of your conversionsso if you are a little confused about speaking to a NPC it is all there every blessed word.  There is one that has every combataction and the result and there is one that has all the NPC's that you have dispached.  The quests are handled in a list of completed quests and open quests you are workinmg on.  A nice feature is the quests that are open are in different colors so you can tell when one is compleated or  can't be compleated or is reasdy to complete.There are things I may not like but I do not mention them unless they seem out of place.  I write this review to tell the reader how the game works.  There are games I do not like because I can see that they could have done better but did not due to such thingss as cost of development, or are just game put on the market to make money.  I do not play games in development or bata  games bedcause I have better things to do.   I do not comment on other reviews because I believe they are voicing ther opinion which I see has no place in a review.   Expressing you opinion is not the way I think a review should be done.  I could be wrong and people might take this review as being to high and mighty, but it is just the way I see it."
