76561198141950631,Not Recommended,219780,28394789,"Posted: 15 December, 2016",all,D'amarr from Darshiva,"Good voice-acting. Female NPCs with pretty faces. Watch your player character in underwear, if you take off every piece of armor. The background music doesn't match the atmosphere always.I've enjoyed the initial exploration in a rather restricted area (aka ""Broken Valley"") that seemed interesting enough. And I've enjoyed the blind flight, because I was playing carefully and without following any guides or walkthroughs.Then I've struggled during the second half. Tedious, dull, repetitive drudgery to attempt a completionist playthrough in order to be able to reach high levels. And even then the experience points mechanics require a variety of special tricks to turn in quest XP at the right time and kill enemies in the right order for more XP. Nevertheless, eventually I almost felt over-powered due to the high level and access to tons of special equipment. The occasional balancing issues made a very few minor boss fights unexpectedly difficult, and I assure you, there are players, who ""rage quit"" the game in such a situation. You can always search for help or hints, but be prepared to find unhelpful comments from either braggarts, or from people, who only know the older release of this game.Haven't run into crashes or obvious bugs. Except in the heat of combat, sometimes either my mouse stopped accepting camera rotation input. Or music stopped playing. Quicksave and quickload fixed it directly during combat.And finally, I've run into a game-breaking bug that is known for years, unfortunately. It's been discussed before. I've mentioned it in the forum, too, before writing this review. An enemy four levels below me, who kills me either with the first magic attack I cannot avoid or with the next attack a second later. There are videos, where that doesn't happen. There are players, who play the game with half the health points and with many more wasted skill points. But there are reports that describe exactly the same problem that can cause real frustration.It seems, the players of this edition of the game are supposed to fire up the game in the separate developer mode and activate a cheat mode to work around that problem. Not sexy at all.Edit #1: A bit later, the same bug apparently also affected another important fight and made it almost impossible even with lots of cheat modes activated. Enemies moved too quickly and were much too resistant to damage to stop them as required during that fight where they approach from three directions and respawn, too. Again, when searching the web about it, I see the same reports by other players and also videos where the enemies move much slower and can be eliminated with ease. Here it seemed impossible even with godlike cheats, multiple summons and holding down the key to launch magical area attacks all the time. Whatever it is that messed up my game on ""Normal"" difficulty so late, it's the opposite of fun.Edit #2: In the end, I've decided not to turn off the cheat modes anymore for the final fight. The frustrating experience has been too much of a motivation killer, and I've also decided against continueing into the add-on due to this."
